WEBVTT

00:02.520 --> 00:04.800
# We're not going out

00:04.840 --> 00:06.680
# Not staying in

00:06.720 --> 00:09.560
# Just hanging around
With my head in a spin

00:09.600 --> 00:11.920
# But there is no need
to scream and shout

00:11.960 --> 00:15.440
# We're not going out

00:15.480 --> 00:18.640
♪ We are not going out. ♪

00:22.720 --> 00:25.560
Yeah, OK, understood.
Thanks, Geoffrey.

00:25.600 --> 00:27.120
'Hang on.'

00:27.160 --> 00:29.880
Are you talking to me whilst
you're in the bathroom?

00:29.920 --> 00:31.920
Yeah. 'Good God.

00:33.240 --> 00:34.640
'What are you wearing?'

00:36.360 --> 00:39.280
This conversation's
taken a bit of a turn.

00:39.320 --> 00:41.640
'Lee, are you speaking to me naked?'

00:41.680 --> 00:43.960
I don't know. I can't see you.

00:44.000 --> 00:45.040
Who's that?

00:45.080 --> 00:46.120
It's your dad.

00:47.640 --> 00:49.160
Sorry, I've got to go, Geoffrey,

00:49.200 --> 00:52.000
Lucy wants to use the
bathroom to kill a pig.

00:52.040 --> 00:53.680
Bye-bye.

00:53.720 --> 00:56.000
Did you want to speak to him?
Not in the bathroom, no.

00:56.040 --> 00:57.320
Why did you bring him in here?

00:57.360 --> 01:00.000
You know he's not actually inside
the magic speaking box, don't you?

01:00.040 --> 01:02.200
It's not that odd,
using the phone in the bathroom.

01:02.240 --> 01:05.400
Well, not for a man who goes to the
toilet when he's in a phone box.

01:05.440 --> 01:08.120
Next time my dad calls,
can you take it in the living room?

01:08.160 --> 01:09.400
Have a bit of dignity.

01:16.880 --> 01:18.960
You have got to be kidding me.

01:19.000 --> 01:20.400
What's the problem?

01:20.440 --> 01:21.600
I'm still here?

01:21.640 --> 01:22.920
And?

01:22.960 --> 01:25.960
Just think there should be a bit of
mystery surrounding this thing.

01:26.000 --> 01:27.200
What do you want me to do,

01:27.240 --> 01:30.240
reach round and whip out
a bunch of flowers?

01:30.280 --> 01:31.760
Why are you suddenly so bothered?

01:31.800 --> 01:34.640
I sometimes go to the toilet when
you're in the shower. Do you?

01:34.680 --> 01:38.600
Don't look so shocked. You go to the
toilet while you're in the shower!

01:40.040 --> 01:43.280
If it's bothering you so much,
leave. I'm cleaning my teeth.

01:43.320 --> 01:45.560
Well, use the kitchen sink.
You use the kitchen sink!

01:47.280 --> 01:48.320
Ok!

01:51.080 --> 01:53.640
Er, excuse me?

01:53.680 --> 01:55.280
Could you close the door, please?

01:55.320 --> 01:57.000
Unbelievable!

02:02.560 --> 02:06.160
There's your orange juice.
Has it got bits in? No.

02:06.200 --> 02:07.560
I want bits in.

02:11.160 --> 02:13.120
There. Now it's got bits in.

02:13.160 --> 02:14.720
I'm off to work.

02:14.760 --> 02:17.440
Those rockets aren't going to fire
themselves, are they, Molly?

02:17.480 --> 02:20.440
You don't have to keep pretending
you're an astronaut, Daddy.

02:20.480 --> 02:22.120
We love you, whatever you do.

02:22.160 --> 02:23.680
I sell cars.

02:23.720 --> 02:25.640
That's rubbish!

02:27.240 --> 02:30.080
Right, I'm going. OK, see you later.

02:30.120 --> 02:31.600
Is that it?

02:31.640 --> 02:33.640
What? Well, aren't
you going to miss me?

02:33.680 --> 02:35.560
I don't know.
Are you going to leave?

02:35.600 --> 02:37.440
You could say goodbye
to me properly.

02:41.440 --> 02:44.160
Wow. But not in front of the kids.
We'll traumatise them.

02:44.200 --> 02:45.920
What's your problem this morning?

02:45.960 --> 02:47.440
I'll tell you my problem.

02:47.480 --> 02:49.440
Where's the intimacy gone
in our relationship?

02:49.480 --> 02:52.960
I just did a great big wee in front
of you. That's fairly intimate.

02:53.000 --> 02:54.520
It's not very romantic, is it?

02:54.560 --> 02:57.120
Well, I'm sorry that I don't go to
the toilet romantically enough.

02:57.160 --> 02:59.480
Maybe next time
I'll sit there playing the harp.

03:00.480 --> 03:03.280
After all, you sometimes sound like
you're in there with a tuba.

03:04.840 --> 03:08.280
Look, it's not just the toilet
thing. It's romance in general.

03:08.320 --> 03:10.040
Do you know that since
we've had the kids,

03:10.080 --> 03:12.520
we haven't had a single night away,
just the two of us? So?

03:12.560 --> 03:15.360
That's your choice,
just as much as mine. No, it's not.

03:15.400 --> 03:18.000
Do you remember what I asked
for on my last birthday?

03:18.040 --> 03:19.440
Oh, not this again.

03:19.480 --> 03:21.560
The Orient Express
is very expensive!

03:21.600 --> 03:22.880
We did the next best thing.

03:22.920 --> 03:26.040
The next best thing to the
Orient Express is not Pizza Express!

03:27.520 --> 03:30.040
And you know it's not just
about the money.

03:31.480 --> 03:34.320
OK, so I don't like leaving the kids
with other people.

03:34.360 --> 03:36.640
I want to be near them
in case they need me.

03:36.680 --> 03:39.280
Mummy, there's a burnt
bit on my toast.

03:39.320 --> 03:42.280
Well, phone social services!

03:42.320 --> 03:44.560
All right, what about tonight?
Me and you

03:44.600 --> 03:47.600
go out for something to eat.
I'll find us a nice restaurant.

03:47.640 --> 03:48.960
Sounds nice.

03:49.000 --> 03:50.280
But...?

03:50.320 --> 03:52.600
Well, if we go out,
we only have to come back.

03:52.640 --> 03:55.000
And we're already here.

03:55.040 --> 03:57.520
All that dressing up,
choosing a restaurant...

03:57.560 --> 04:00.040
Yeah, it's not easy, is it?
Putting clothes on and eating.

04:00.080 --> 04:01.960
Maybe we should just stay at
home in our pants

04:02.000 --> 04:03.440
and suck on a damp flannel.

04:05.200 --> 04:07.800
OK, we'll stay at home,
but we're doing it properly.

04:07.840 --> 04:08.960
I'll cook us dinner.

04:09.000 --> 04:12.000
We don't watch television, and we
don't eat until the kids are in bed.

04:12.040 --> 04:13.680
OK, if you insist.

04:13.720 --> 04:14.760
If I insist?

04:14.800 --> 04:17.079
I'm not asking you to
dress as a lollipop lady

04:17.120 --> 04:18.600
and spank me with the sign!

04:20.959 --> 04:23.120
It's supposed to be romantic. OK.

04:23.160 --> 04:25.000
So I'm saying yes, fine, OK? Great.

04:25.040 --> 04:28.480
Well, I'll look forward to it, then.
Well then, so will I. Fine.

04:32.600 --> 04:35.240
Are you two getting divorced?

04:35.280 --> 04:37.280
Just eat your orange juice.

04:43.960 --> 04:45.760
Coming, ready or not!

04:48.000 --> 04:50.920
Are they hiding in the cupboard
under the stairs?

04:50.960 --> 04:54.560
No, they're not in the
cupboard under the stairs.

04:54.600 --> 04:57.560
Are they hiding under
the kitchen table?

04:57.600 --> 05:01.480
No, they're not hiding
under the kitchen table.

05:01.520 --> 05:03.240
Where can they be?

05:03.280 --> 05:06.800
Maybe I should
look behind the curtains.

05:06.840 --> 05:09.680
No, they're not behind the curtains.

05:09.720 --> 05:11.680
We are behind the curtains!

05:14.760 --> 05:16.240
I meant under the carpet.

05:17.680 --> 05:18.920
Come on.

05:20.080 --> 05:21.840
Charlie's been sick at Beavers.

05:21.880 --> 05:24.400
Don't worry, son,
I once sneezed at an otter.

05:26.120 --> 05:27.840
Oh, why's it so gloomy in here?

05:30.360 --> 05:32.080
I was going for an ambience.

05:32.120 --> 05:35.080
Is the ambulance for me?

05:35.120 --> 05:37.240
Not an ambulance, an ambience.

05:37.280 --> 05:41.520
It means when you're trying to
create...an ambience.

05:44.800 --> 05:46.840
Oh!

05:46.880 --> 05:49.080
Oh, so that's where they are.
I had no idea!

05:49.120 --> 05:51.120
We did tell you.

05:51.160 --> 05:54.800
Oh, that was your voice, was it?
I'll cancel the priest.

05:54.840 --> 05:56.520
Let's get them to bed.

05:56.560 --> 05:59.480
I can't help tonight, can I?
I'm cooking, remember? Yeah...

05:59.520 --> 06:02.400
OK, I'll sort the kids out.
What are you doing?

06:02.440 --> 06:05.840
Just grabbing a banana. I'm
starving. Well, don't grab a banana.

06:05.880 --> 06:08.720
It will spoil your dinner.
Why, is that what we're having?

06:10.640 --> 06:12.000
Molly, you know when you do that

06:12.040 --> 06:13.840
and it's not your birthday,
a fairy dies?

06:13.880 --> 06:16.560
MOLLY WAILS

06:16.600 --> 06:19.720
Come on, kids. Daddy's busy.

06:19.760 --> 06:21.600
I'm just trying to
create an atmosphere.

06:21.640 --> 06:24.320
Well, I'm hungry and the kids
are upset, so well done.

06:24.360 --> 06:25.520
Mission accomplished.

06:30.240 --> 06:31.960
ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYS

06:32.000 --> 06:34.640
Oh. You've changed.

06:34.680 --> 06:37.400
No big deal. Same pants.

06:37.440 --> 06:39.480
They must be due their
annual service soon.

06:41.960 --> 06:43.760
Oh, looks lovely. Thanks.

06:43.800 --> 06:45.160
It's a Jamie Oliver thing.

06:45.200 --> 06:46.480
I was going to do Heston,

06:46.520 --> 06:49.000
but I didn't have a
hydrovacuated testicular spatula.

06:51.240 --> 06:53.120
It's a Moroccan lamb dish.

06:53.160 --> 06:56.520
Made with loads of different spices
and cooked in a sauce made from...

06:57.760 --> 07:00.200
Made from chicken beaks
and cats' faces.

07:00.240 --> 07:01.960
Oh, sounds lovely.

07:02.000 --> 07:03.640
Are you texting?

07:03.680 --> 07:04.720
No.

07:04.760 --> 07:06.280
Yes, you are. You're on the phone.

07:06.320 --> 07:08.920
I know, but I'm not texting.
I was on Tinder!

07:10.200 --> 07:12.440
I'm just looking up
Charlie's symptoms.

07:12.480 --> 07:14.120
Well, whilst you're
on the NHS website,

07:14.160 --> 07:16.240
you might want to look up the
medical effects of having

07:16.280 --> 07:18.640
a lamb tagine force-fed
down your oesophagus.

07:19.840 --> 07:21.800
Charlie will be fine.

07:21.840 --> 07:23.880
Come on, it's supposed to be
a romantic meal.

07:23.920 --> 07:26.240
Took me ages to do this cooking.
Thanks.

07:26.280 --> 07:29.720
And I do appreciate you going to the
same effort I go to every night.

07:31.800 --> 07:33.680
In fact, if this
is the effect it has,

07:33.720 --> 07:36.440
I should go to the toilet
in front of you more often!

07:36.480 --> 07:38.080
It wasn't just the toilet thing.

07:38.120 --> 07:41.040
I just worry sometimes that we're
not concentrating on each other

07:41.080 --> 07:42.360
as much as we should be.

07:42.400 --> 07:44.200
Is this you asking me for more sex?

07:44.240 --> 07:46.200
No.

07:46.240 --> 07:49.120
Well, were you about to suggest...?
No. It's not about sex.

07:49.160 --> 07:52.200
It's about me and you not forgetting
to be romantic with each other,

07:52.240 --> 07:54.160
like we are being now.

07:54.200 --> 07:57.360
Look, Lee, I really appreciate
everything you've done tonight.

07:57.400 --> 07:59.760
And it's sweet that you're
so concerned about us, but,

07:59.800 --> 08:01.400
honestly, we're doing fine!

08:01.440 --> 08:02.720
I love you.

08:02.760 --> 08:05.280
Along with the kids, you're
the most important thing in my life,

08:05.320 --> 08:08.240
and I don't take that
for granted, ever.

08:08.280 --> 08:10.640
And I certainly don't
think I've lost the romance.

08:10.680 --> 08:12.040
Are you sure?

08:12.080 --> 08:13.240
I'm sure.

08:13.280 --> 08:14.440
Ok.

08:19.800 --> 08:21.040
Happy anniversary.

08:28.320 --> 08:30.240
Well, aren't you going to open it?

08:33.120 --> 08:34.960
It's not today, is it?

08:35.000 --> 08:37.120
Oh, I think it is.

08:37.159 --> 08:39.760
Well, you're obviously overwhelmed.
I'll open it for you.

08:39.799 --> 08:41.240
Are you sure it isn't tomorrow?

08:41.280 --> 08:43.679
Oh, no, tomorrow is a different
special day altogether.

08:43.720 --> 08:47.640
It's the one-day anniversary of the
that day you forgot our anniversary.

08:48.640 --> 08:51.160
Look, it's that
special vintage hourglass

08:51.200 --> 08:52.880
we saw in that antiques shop.

08:52.920 --> 08:55.880
Well, I haven't really
forgotten our anniversary.

08:55.920 --> 08:57.520
Oh, so?

08:59.320 --> 09:01.680
I'll give you three minutes
to think of something.

09:08.720 --> 09:12.240
Well, maybe there's a present
waiting for you to unwrap

09:12.280 --> 09:14.440
when we get upstairs.

09:14.480 --> 09:17.000
Oh? An actual present? Could be.

09:17.040 --> 09:20.040
Or do you mean me taking your
clothes off, because unless you've

09:20.080 --> 09:23.120
got some Debenhams vouchers tucked
under there, that doesn't count!

09:24.560 --> 09:26.840
Is this why you've been
acting odd all day?

09:26.880 --> 09:28.960
Going on about the lack of romance?

09:29.000 --> 09:31.800
Oh, Lucy, forget about it.
It doesn't matter.

09:31.840 --> 09:34.840
This is just a silly little
something to say that the

09:34.880 --> 09:37.120
sands of time
are like my love for you.

09:37.160 --> 09:38.720
Always flowing.

09:38.760 --> 09:41.840
And if at times our love
has the appearance of ebbing away,

09:41.880 --> 09:44.720
you just have to put a little bit
of effort in and very soon

09:44.760 --> 09:49.520
you can turn things round and
see the love flowing once again.

09:49.560 --> 09:50.680
I hate you!

